Suppose that instead of contracting a table by halving its size when its load factor drops below $1 / 4$, we contract it by multiplying its size by $2 / 3$ when its load factor drops below $1 / 3$. Using the potential function  $$\Phi(T) = | 2 \cdot T.num - T.size |,$$  show that the amortized cost of a $\text{TABLE-DELETE}$ that uses this strategy is bounded above by a constant.   If $1 / 3 < \alpha_i \le 1 / 2$,  \begin{align}
